<br>
#1 - When you are hit from the sides. It's much more difficult to 'step' into melee when the direction of the blows isn't straight in line with your direction of travel. This is best countered by facing the person hitting you, and wall pinning yourself or other tactics so you can't be moved.<br>
<br>
#2 - Biggest wizard killer. Stunning blows (bash, kick, crippling blow, etc). No AA in the world is really going to save you much here, p.s - clerics getting bash = gay.<br>
<br>
Remember a couple of other points. The average PC melee has a higher ATK rating than most mobs. A 65 melee buffed has probably 1700ish ATK, ranging to over 2k depending on the class/gear. With our AC softcap somewhere below 1000, you are simply going to get hit a ot by PC's, and a lot more than mobs (with their lower ATK) are going to hit you. So these AA's - especially LR5 - which help against mobs will give you a lower return against PC's.<br>
<br>
We have a couple of casters with LR5, they've all said it's almost unnoticable in PvP, high ATK melees still hit really hard, and still hit almost all the time. If you have points to burn, go for it. But unless you already have QD3, Crit9, Allegiant Familiar, ND3, Strong Root, Channeling3 and a few other AA's first, it's probably a waste for all the AA it takes.<br>
<br>
Channeling3 on the other hand ... fucking owns. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;font-family:courier;font-size:small;">&quot;It never stops hurting, you just go faster...&quot;</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--> - <!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-family:courier;font-size:small;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Greg LeMond</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#ffffff>- </font><a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation>Graffë's Wizard Discussion</a><font color=#ffffff> - </font><a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1>General EQ Discussion</a> <font color=#ffffff> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 7.240<br>Copyright ©1999-2003 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  

